<br>
&quot;HAHA...&quot; I smirked slightly to myself. Had I known this then I probably would have cared as much as I did now which was nothing at all. New York was now the perfect place for a dhampire such as myself to wander. Powerful enough to defend herself and able to walk around in day and night. Though of course the smog made day not so bright anymore but still. This was also a place I could walk freely about with my weapons on myself and no one cared. No police with whistles to come up and take everything away from me, not that I would have let them...<br>
<br>
However without life, this city no longer had the fun it had before. Gone were the days I could kill and read about it the following morning and laugh while the police had difficulty finding clues. Now death was how everyone lived, there was no escape. Vampires were no longer a myth and humans knew they had to become one to survive. Just yesterday I had seen a twelve year old girl, a pretty little thing naked as the day she was born and carrying a sign. It had said <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>free blood in exchange for siring.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Well I took her back to my place, fed from her slender little neck while I held her dark hair in my hands and nearly killed her but didn't. Instead I had her bathed and dressed to be toyed with later. I can not sire her but young virgin blood is the sweetiest blood of all.<br>
<br>
But now I was bored and looking for some action be it sexual or other. My young sweet blooded toy at home would not serve me in my desires not that she didn't want to but I was not into that stuff. My own history of when I was her age was painful enough and I would not put her through that as well. &quot;Come on... Mother Russia has more fun then this...&quot; I muttered to myself as I leaped up to rest upon a street light that flickered dimly through dusty glass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dhampirlordofmallorea>Dhampir Lord of Mallorea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/31/03 10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Cale smiled at Iris's comments. He was about to make a comeback when his cell rang. Groaning loudly, he excused him self, and made a mental note to stake the vampire who called him.<br>
