<br>
The man looked up at Cale and then let his eyes drift to Iris. &quot;Did I interupt something, Cale? I'm so sorry.&quot; Eric's tone suggested he was anything but as he stood up.<br>
<br>
Cale only gave a small smile and a chuckle at the mortal's humor. &quot;You did. But no matter. It's an advantage of being a vampire to be able to mix buisness...&quot; At this he bent and took Iris's hand and planted a small kiss on it. &quot;...With pleasure,&quot; Cale finished smoothly as his lips left his companions hand. Then he quickly spun and landed a solid punch to Eric's chest, sending him back into a wall. &quot;You see? I got immense pleasure from that.&quot;<br>
<br>
After spitting up some of his own blood, Eric only offered an obscenity in response, to which Cale sighed and shook his head. &quot;Now is that any way to speak infront of a lady?&quot; Cale asked as his foot connected with Eric's jaw.<br>
<br>
Eric muttered something of which Cale only caught, &quot;...you and your girlfriend!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Eric. Is that a nice thing to say?&quot; the vampire responded. &quot;When you say things like that, I get angry, and when vampires like me get angry, humans like you lose their heads.&quot; At this last Cale grabbed the revolver he had found earlier and aimed it at Eric's head, who immediately straightened up at the sight of the weapon, obviously reckognizing it.<br>
<br>
When he finally spoke, Eric spoke quietly. &quot;The person who owns that gun, and it's twin, will find you and reclaim it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So you know the man who killed my brother. Too bad you're going to die soon. This is really a magnificent weapon. Of course, as I am sure you know, it's not so much the gun as the bullets.&quot; Cale pulled back the hammer and squeezed the trigger. Once released, the hammer hit with a resounding *click*. Eric was surprised his head remained intact. Cale laughed. &quot;No, I have a far worse fate in mind for you, my friend.&quot; Then turning to a vampire, Cale simply said, &quot;You know what to do.&quot;<br>
<br>
Walking away, Cale passed Iris and paused. Turning around he adressed his lackies. &quot;Out of curiosity, which of you called me?&quot; Four of them reckognized the tone in Cale's voice as masked anger and got out of the way, but the fifth did not.<br>
<br>
&quot;It was me, sir,&quot; he said with a smile, thinking he was about to be rewarded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good job,&quot; Cale said turning around. But then faster than the human eye could comprehend, he spun with the gun in hand and pointed it at the vampires head. &quot;But unfortunately, you interupted a dance.&quot; He cocked the hammer, hearing it click as the chamber turned, lining a bullet up. Then he pulled the trigger until the hammer was released and struck the bullet on the firing pin. The gunpowder ignited, sending the bullet and sever gasses out of the barrel, causing a loud explosion as it cleared the barrel. The bullet spiraled until it reached the vamps skull, which ignited the original explosive and then the thermite. The rest was a flash of light no one could look at directly.<br>
<br>
Cale smiled as he looked at the ashes. Then turning to Iris, &quot;Shall we?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/2/03 10:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Iris tore her gaze away from the remnants of the carnage, a new respect for Cale obvious in her eyes at having done something so destructive so easily. Her eyes flicked in Eric's direction for the barest of seconds before her darkly violet gaze returned to Cale. She gave him a small grin and nodded. She still had a lot to learn, but for the time being... &quot;Yes. Let's shall.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dhampirlordofmallorea>Dhampir Lord of Mallorea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/2/03 10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Cale extended his arm as he reached with his other hand into his jacket pocket to grab his ciggarettes (incidently the same brand George perfers). He shook one from the container and put it in his mouth. Then, deciding since he began by being at least a slight gentleman, he may as well continue, Cale offered Iris one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/2/03 11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Iris shrugged and took one, holding it between her lips with a practiced ease. She'd smoked when she was a mortal, and it had made her voice a tad deeper so that it sounded more at home in a bedroom than anywhere else. She produced a lighter from seemingly nowhere and flicked the cover of the zippo open, lighting it in the same instant. Fire always had held a morbid fascination for her since she'd been changed... She lit the cancer stick and took a long, blissful drag, making the end glow red in the semi-darkness. She tilted her head back slightly and blew a perfect smoke ring from her full lips.<br>
<br>
She held the cigarette between her fingers, almost making it seem like it belonged there. She gave Cale a smile and pressed a soft kiss to his cheek. &quot;Thanks, hun. So... where to, now?&quot; She took a short drag, inhaling the toxic smoke deeply. She couldn't get cancer from it, so why not have one on occasion? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midnightrayne>Midnight Rayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Blood</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/2/03 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forumshomepage.homestead.com/files/midnightrayne.jpg height=200 WIDTH=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> (you guys sure post quick...)<br>
<br>
From my perch on the flickering street light I witnessed the shooting with mild interest. Such might have been impressive or perhaps frightening even to some a while ago but to me it was nothing. Bullets tearing through flesh as blood sprang free into the air was my every day surroundings as a child growing up in Russia and then when I joined the Germans in World War II. But even so I was not about to go messing around this night with those who had guns for I myself had other needs.<br>
<br>
One of my needs was to satisfy my thirst for blood for I was feeling a little light headed without it. Second I wanted some action be it violent or sexual. In either case I planned on combining all of those desires into one and have myself a little fun. With ease I sprang from the tops of the street lights, one to the next while keeping just in glimpsing sight of the others. It was not completely intentional on my part but ah well, like I really cared who saw me at this point. Tight leather that was open to allow just the right amount of flesh to show without appearing like a complete slut was my attaire though I was quite certain my weapons gave people the right idea. I was not one to be taken lightly and since tonight I was not in a gameful mood, I allowed the world to see what I truely was.<br>
<br>
As I leaped lightly from lamp to lamp, my eyes roamed the streets looking for possible victims and soon my eyes landed upon a young couple sitting on a park bench. The male was clearly vampire for I could smell it but the girl was his toy. She was a pretty little thing and bonded to him so I knew what my course of action would be. The sweet taste of mortal blood mixed with vampire blood was what I wanted and she had it but first I would have to get rid of him. Silently I landed behind them and in the darkness, I stalked them knowing his vampire life was soon to come to an end and I would suck from tender young breast of the girl's till her life would end with the same bloody weapon his was about to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midnightrayne>Midnight Rayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Blood</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/3/03 1:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://forumshomepage.homestead.com/files/midnightrayne.jpg height=200 WIDTH=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> (sorry can't stay in this thread... moving to a slower one)<br>
